Bayer, Nordex, Volkswagen: Equity Market Preview for Germany

-- B y   N i c h o l a s   C o m f o r t
-- 
2011-03-29T04:00:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-29/bayer-nordex-volkswagen-equity-market-preview-for-germany.html
The following is a list of
companies whose shares may have unusual price changes in
 Germany . Stock symbols are in parentheses and share prices are
from the previous close.  The benchmark DAX Index slipped 0.1 percent to 6,938.63.  Bayer AG (BAYN)  : The German drug and chemical maker will
increase its sales in Brazil, Russia, India and  China  to about
10 billion euros by 2015 from 5.5 billion euros currently,
Handelsblatt reported, citing Chief Executive Officer Marijn Dekkers. The shares fell 0.4 percent to 53.08 euros.  Nordex SE (NDX1)  (NDX1 GY): The wind turbine maker plans to sell
6.68 million shares in an accelerated bookbuild and will use the
proceeds to invest in research and development. The stock surged
12 percent to 9.37 euros.  Volkswagen AG (VOW)  (VOW3 GY):  Europe ’s largest car maker is
recalling 71,043 Jettas in the U.S. because an electrical short
in the horn can cause the cars to stall or their headlights or
windshield wipers to stop working, Sheriece Matias, a U.S.-based
spokeswoman for the company, said. VW’s preferred shares fell
0.8 percent to 112.15 euros.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Nicholas Comfort in Frankfurt at 
 ncomfort1@bloomberg.net ;  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Kennedy at   wkennedy3@bloomberg.net  